The paper deals with image retrieval tasks using hashing techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of deep learning and neural networks in the proposed method also makes it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of supervised learning and loss functions suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
